# Feature Parity

- Scaffold VS Code feature categories as Velocity modules; implement progressively.
- Every feature needs mode (core/dev/heavy/agent/remote/legacy), activation policy, and budgets.
- Disabled by default unless part of the core editing loop.
- Independently killable via Feature Toggle Matrix.
- See `docs/velocity/11-vscode-feature-parity-research.md` and `14-feature-parity-matrix.md`.
